The paper discusses the efficiency of ResNet in learning CIFAR-10, which is a computer vision dataset, and compares it to kernel methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the computation complexity advantage of ResNet, which could also place it in the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT).
